<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-26T22:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-26T22:36:00-05:00" n="1006" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1006">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/3389.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-26T21:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 26, 1912—9 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The press censorship is rigid, and it is evident that consular telegrams
                            are being refused upon some pretext. I receive no reports from consuls
                            either on Pacific coast or the south.</p>
                        <p>Acting on consular reports from Tampico I have directly requested the
                            governor of San Luis Potosí to protect Americans and have his telegram
                            in agreement.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>